      • createRooms

        public static java.util.ArrayList<Room> createRooms(java.lang.String filename)
        Creates rooms with input from a file. 
         The file is not empty and each line of the file represents a room on the format: 
 roomName;northRoomName;eastRoomName;southRoomName;westRoomName;northDoor;eastDoor;southDoor;westDoor 
 roomName must match one of the roomNames in the file
 At least one of the rooms must have only one door.
        Parameters:
        filename - The name of the file containing information about the rooms
        Returns:
        a list of rooms

      • createCourses

        public static java.util.ArrayList<Course> createCourses(java.lang.String filename,
                                                        java.util.ArrayList<Book> books)
        Creates courses with input from a file and connects each course with its book. 
         The file is not empty and each line of the file represents a course on the format: 
 courseName;bookName;credits;question;alternativ1;alternative2;alternativ3;correctAlternative 
 CorrectAlternative is "a" if alternative1 is the correct answer 
 bookName matches the name of a book in the list of books
        Parameters:
        filename - The name of the file containing information about the books
        books - A list of books
        Returns:
        A list of courses

      • createStudents

        public static java.util.ArrayList<Student> createStudents(java.lang.String filename,
                                                          java.util.ArrayList<Course> courses)
        Creates students with input from a file and connect each student with a completed course and a ongoing course.
        Parameters:
        filename - The name of the file containing information about the teachers
        courses - A list of courses 
         The file is not empty and each line of the file represents a name of a teacher on the format: 
 
         Karro 
         Patrik 
         The number of students is around half the amount of courses.
        Returns:
        A list of students
